Row.uwwHistorie: Waste water treatment plant of Kasevälja is closed, waste water is directed to the waste water treatment plant of Suurupi (EEPUH0000199).
Since August 30 2014 the school of Jaanikese has been connected with sewerage system of Valga.
The waste water treatment plant of Merekodu has not been in use since February 2014. Waste water is directed to the waste water treatment plant of Suurupi (EEPUH0000199).
Since April 2014 waste water has been directed to the waste water treatment plant of Keila-Joa (EEPUH0370180).
Deactivated due to changes in generated load (below 2000).

Row.mslRemarks: There is no waste water re-use in Estonia.
